Parvaim: Parvaim is supposed by Calmet to be the same as Sepharvaim in
Armenia or Media; Bochart is of opinion that it is Taprobanes, now the
island of Ceylon, which he drives from taph, a border, and Parvan, i.e.,
"the coast of Parvan;" but the late Editor of Calmet thinks it the same
as the Parvatoi mountains of Ptolemy, at the head of the Indus.

